I had to stop because even after a minute it did not finish.

[This](https://github.com/mglagla/calcium/commit/9af1873a20e051d0ad8b9809af3adb8148bd5cdf) is the offending commit on branch "no-alloc", the previous commit on branch master finished very quickly.

The only difference to master is this code in parse.rs, [starting on line 97:](https://github.com/mglagla/calcium/blob/master/src/parse.rs#L97)

``` rust
let mut ref_c = 1;
let mut sub_tokens = Vec::new();

while ref_c > 0 {
    let token = if let Some(t) = it.next() {
        t.clone()
    } else { return Err(ParseError::MismatchingParens) };

        match token {
            Token::Operator(Symbol::OpenParen) => {
                ref_c += 1;
            },
            Token::Operator(Symbol::CloseParen) => {
                ref_c -= 1;
            },
            _ => {},
        }

    if ref_c > 0 {
        sub_tokens.push(token);
    }
}

let mut sub_iter = sub_tokens.iter().peekable();
parse_expr(&mut sub_iter, 0)              
```

[has been replaced with this code:](https://github.com/mglagla/calcium/blob/no-alloc/src/parse.rs#L97)

``` rust
let mut ref_c = 1;
let mut sub_iter = it.filter_map(|t| {
    match *t {
        Token::Operator(Symbol::OpenParen) => {
            ref_c += 1;
        },
        Token::Operator(Symbol::CloseParen) => {
            ref_c -= 1;
        },
        _ => {},
    };

    if ref_c > 0 {
        Some(t)
    } else {
        None
    }
})
.fuse()
.peekable();

parse_expr(&mut sub_iter, 0)
```

rustc version is 1.12.0 (3191fbae9 2016-09-23)
